				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You people are too ego-centric.
<br />

<br />
There are people out there who don't raid, who's pets could last for weeks on end.  The fact that you raid and they don't does not imply that other's cannot have this happen.
<br />

<br />
The reasoning is still stupid, there are much better fixes if this is truly the issue they don't like, but they can and do apply to some people...
<br />

<br />
I've gone 6 weeks before without a death of either mine or my pet, as I am not a raider...if persistant minion existed at that point I'd be exactly the type of person who Brenlo was referring to.
<br />

<br />
If you think it's "insulting your intelligence" for him to claim this then you are looking to be offended.  The game does not and never really has revolved around raiders.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
